  "texts": [
    "VR and AR technologies have the potential to make interactive, customizable, 3D virtual patients ''digital twins'' effective for educating healthcare professionals with vast applications and to improve the clinicians' skills.",
    "Also, they are valuable for undergraduate basic and clinical sciences learning [71,72].",
    "VR and AR technologies are used to create environments that simulate paininducing scenarios to analyze user responses, such as physiological changes or behavioral reactions.",
    "These technologies can also be used as distraction techniques during painful procedures because they command an individual's focus, reducing their awareness of pain [73].",
    "The immersive nature of VR and AR can transport patients to different environments, engage them in interactive activities, and, thus, alter their perceptions of pain [73,74]."
  ],
